What This Project Does
Your project is fetching:
* Product Name
* Customer Name
* Ratings
* Comments/Reviews
from a live ecommerce webpage using Python.

Viva Questions They May Ask
Why use BeautifulSoup?
To extract HTML data from websites.

Why use requests library?
To send HTTP requests and get webpage content.

What is web scraping?
Automatically extracting data from websites.

What is HTML parser?
It converts webpage HTML into readable Python objects.

If College Asks “Real Time Reviews”
Say:
"The scraper fetches live reviews directly from the ecommerce webpage every time the program runs."

If They Ask Why Amazon/Flipkart Not Used
Say:
"Major ecommerce websites use anti-bot protection and CAPTCHA, so demo ecommerce sites are used for educational purposes."

Optional Improvement (Very Important for Marks)
You can also save reviews into CSV.
Add this code at the end:
import csv

with open("reviews.csv", "w", newline="", encoding="utf-8") as file:

    writer = csv.writer(file)

    writer.writerow(["Customer Name", "Rating", "Comment"])

    for review in reviews:

        customer = review.find("span", class_="review-author").text.strip()

        rating = len(review.find_all("span", class_="ws-icon-star"))

        comment = review.find("p", class_="review-content").text.strip()

        writer.writerow([customer, rating, comment])

print("\nData saved to reviews.csv")
This creates:
reviews.csv
which opens in Excel.
